This game I knew nothing about has instantly skyrocketed to my list of favorites on ios.  The elegant controls allow for a lot of easily executed yet complicated maneuvers that are introduced at a great pace.  Production value is very high as well!  I was not initially drawn to it but kept reading rave reviews - it's highly deserving of praise.  This is the game of 2013 thus far - it's admittedly early, but I am excited to see if it can be topped this year.

An extremely well-done game, with excellent visuals, controls (no quickly done port here) and a surprisingly deep amount of content.  Ran extremely well on my aging iPhone 4, which is impressive given the amount of content on screen.  Had just the right amount of challenge for me (levels near the end like Alpha Mission felt "tough but possible").  Will probably pick up the PS3 version as well.
One of my favorite iOS games.  A must play title for your iDevice.

Got it on sale and glad I did, because its not worth full price in my opinion. Gameplay is far too repetitive and frankly not that creative. Having to touch objects to collect them while driving is distracting and disjointed. On top of that, the touch controls don't even work that well half the time. Lots of content, but like I said it can be repetitive and buying characters seems to function more as artificial lengthening for "character specific" challenges. An OK game in my opinion.
